Health workers in rural areas are feeling abandoned - saying they have to wait longer to be vaccinated. eNCA's Masego Rahlaga reports. Courtesy of #DStv403 KAGISANO RURAL, North West - Health workers in rural areas are feeling abandoned - saying they have to wait longer to be vaccinated. Frontline workers need to register online to get a voucher to get the jab but this needs the internet and smart gadgets something that's a luxury to many. READ: Nearly 9000 healthcare workers vaccinated in Limpopo In some rural North-West communities- issues around transport are also a concern. Watch the video above for more details in this story